{"label":"GIT - intro","id":"git","list":[{"label":"Multiple Choice Question","type":"mcq","id":"test","commonData":{"title":"Multiple Choice Question","allowFrac":false},"data":[{"questions":[{"qText":"Which command is used to create a new Git repository?","options":"git init\ngit start\ngit create\ngit new"},{"qText":"Which command is used to check the current status of a Git repository?","options":"git status\ngit check\ngit info\ngit verify"},{"qText":"Which command stages changes for the next commit?","options":"git add\ngit stage\ngit push\ngit commit"},{"qText":"Which command is used to save changes in the repository?","options":"git commit\ngit push\ngit save\ngit record"},{"qText":"Which command is used to see the commit history?","options":"git log\ngit history\ngit commits\ngit show-all"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which command is used to create a new branch?","options":"git branch branch_name\ngit create branch_name\ngit new-branch branch_name\ngit make branch_name"},{"qText":"Which command switches to another branch?","options":"git checkout branch_name\ngit change branch_name\ngit switch-to branch_name\ngit move branch_name"},{"qText":"Which command merges one branch into another?","options":"git merge branch_name\ngit combine branch_name\ngit attach branch_name\ngit join branch_name"},{"qText":"Which command uploads local commits to a remote repository?","options":"git push\ngit upload\ngit send\ngit transfer"},{"qText":"Which command downloads changes from a remote repository to local?","options":"git pull\ngit download\ngit fetch-all\ngit sync"}]},{"questions":[{"qText":"Which command is used to clone a repository from GitHub or other sources?","options":"git clone\ngit copy\ngit get\ngit fetch"},{"qText":"Which file is used to ignore files and directories in Git?","options":".gitignore\n.gitconfig\n.gitkeep\n.gitfiles"},{"qText":"Which command shows the differences between the working directory and the staging area?","options":"git diff\ngit changes\ngit compare\ngit show-diff"},{"qText":"Which command removes a file from the staging area but not from the working directory?","options":"git reset\ngit remove\ngit unstage\ngit delete"},{"qText":"Which command is used to configure username in Git?","options":"git config --global user.name \"Your Name\"\ngit set username \"Your Name\"\ngit adduser \"Your Name\"\ngit define username \"Your Name\""}]}]},{"id":"match","label":"Drag and Drop","type":"match","onlyBigScreen":true,"data":{"title":"Drag and Drop","fontSize":"1.5rem","leftSideWidth":500,"allowFrac":false,"text":"Shows the current state of the working directory and staging area | git status\nUploads local commits to the remote repository | git push\nDownloads changes from a remote repository and merges them | git pull\nInitializes a new Git repository in a folder | git init\nCreates or lists branches in a repository | git branch\nCopies a remote repository into a local machine | git clone <url>\nRecords changes to the repository with a message | git commit -m \"message\"\nStages a file to be included in the next commit | git add file.txt"}},{"type":"classifySentence","label":"True or False","id":"true-false","data":{"title":"True or False","types":[{"name":"True","text":"Git is a distributed version control system.\nThe command 'git init' initializes a new Git repository.\nThe command 'git status' shows the state of the working directory and staging area.\nThe command 'git clone' is used to copy a remote repository.\nThe '.gitignore' file is used to exclude files from being tracked."},{"name":"False","text":"Git can only be used when connected to the internet.\nThe command 'git push' is used to stage changes before committing.\nBranches in Git cannot be merged.\nGit does not allow reverting to a previous commit.\nThe command 'git log' is used to delete commits."}]}},{"id":"fillup","label":"Fill in the blanks","type":"fillup","data":{"title":"Fill in the blanks","fontSize":"1.4rem","text":"The command used to initialize a new Git repository is * git init(git start, git create)*.\n        To check the current state of the working directory, we use *git status (git check, git verify)*.\nThe command used to stage changes for the next commit is *git add (git stage, git prepare)*.\nThe command *git commit (git save, git record)* is used to save changes in the local repository.\nTo copy a remote repository to your local machine, you use *git clone (git copy, git fetch) *.\nThe file .* gitignore (gitconfig, gitkeep)* is used to specify files and directories that Git should ignore.\nThe command *git push (git send, git transfer)* is used to upload local commits to a remote repository.\nThe command *git pull(git fetch-all, git download)* is used to download and merge changes from a remote repository.\nThe command *git branch (git create-branch, git new-branch)* creates a new branch in Git.\nThe command * git log(git history, git commits)* shows the commit history of a repository."}}]}